8AYTnunItsQ.title: President Duterte raises hands of administration senatorial bets | ABS-CBN News
8AYTnunItsQ.description:
President Rodrigo Duterte on Friday raised the hands of 8 senatorial aspirants under the slate of PDP-Laban. The Senate hopefuls are broadcaster Rey Langit, Presidential Anti-Corruption Commission Chairman Greco Belgica, actor Robin Padilla, former Public Works Sec. Mark Villar, former Information and Communications Technology Sec. Gringo Honasan, former Agrarian Reform Sec. John Castriciones, Presidential legal counsel Salvador Panelo, and Deputy House Speaker Rodante Marcoleta. Duterte was joined by Sen. Christopher "Bong" Go, who earlier filed his candidacy for vice president.

ZaJpgUJFF0k.title: Outbreak | #NoFilter
ZaJpgUJFF0k.description:
"#NoFilter" features the story of some Filipinos who chose to put their personal safety on the line to better serve their fellowmen amid the danger and fear brought by the coronavirus disease (COVID-19). Raphael Bosano follows the journey of nurse Jay Juan and four other medical professionals from the DOH who volunteered to aid in the repatriation of 30 Filipino workers from coronavirus-stricken Wuhan, China. After his two-week mandatory quarantine at the Athletes' Village in New Clark City, Tarlac, Juan now prepares to oversee the operation center for new repatriates from coronavirus-hit areas. The program also features the compassion of Filipino workers "Tisoy," "Cherrie May," and "Shara" who chose to stay in Wuhan City to help others survive the epidemic amid the lockdown.

4mB0VI0YBik.description:
"SOCO" looks into how the unstable relationship of a couple in Tondo, Manila led to a violent crime. Angel Leguin describes his son Ariel's relationship with the daughter of Randy Panday, a man notorious for threatening residents in Aroma Compound. Angel says that the couple used to argue a lot about money and recalls how it eventually led to the death of his two sons. MPD Homicide Section chief PCapt. Henry Navarro details their initial investigation into the case.

“Failon Ngayon” sifts through a DILG memorandum circular that compels local governments to clear public facilities in their areas of jurisdictions. The program then shows how mayors in Metro Manila take on the challenge to reclaim all public roads in their cities.

Abangan ang mga isyung lahat tayo may pakialam sa FAILON NGAYON tuwing Sabado pagkatapos ng Pinoy Brother Otso alas-11 ng gabi sa ABS-CBN.

Mapapanood ang replay ng FAILON NGAYON sa ANC tuwing Linggo, alas-2 ng hapon. 

Mag-kumento at ipahayag ang inyong saloobin sa aming official Facebook pages, http://www.facebook.com/failon.ngayon.fanpage.

soi3zQOcyeI.title: Lalaki Sa Storage Box | SOCO
soi3zQOcyeI.description:
"SOCO" looks into the case of Carl Laurence Demerey, a 24-year-old student who was found dead inside a plastic storage box in Brgy. Canlalay, Biñan City, Laguna. The Biñan Police proceeds to examine various CCTV footage around a resto bar where Demerey was last seen by his friend, who later surfaced as a witness. PLTCOL. Danilo Mendoza recalls how they identified three persons of interest, and talks about the arrest of the two suspects named Najir Macaorao and Abdul Canapia. The program then presents the testimonies of Macaorao and Canapia. Demerey's mother calls on the last suspect to surrender to the authorities, and vows to seek justice for the death of her son.  

For more SOCO videos, see the link below:

BRWFObWM5Uk.title: Surplus | #NoFilter
BRWFObWM5Uk.description:
"#NoFilter" looks into the "surplus culture" in the Philippines. Brgy. 650 Port Area, Manila administrator Edith Ferrer relays the reason why majority of families in their community opt to buy preloved items. Jeck Batallones speaks with some Filipinos who have found use and opportunities in second-hand appliances and items. The program also delves into the issue of illegally-shipped household wastes and garbage from Canada, South Korea, Hong Kong, and Australia. Lastly, auction house owners Connie Shimosato and Yasutoshi Shimosato show how they operate their second-hand buy and sell business.

ljYHFDgReJI.description:
"SOCO" reenacts how intense lust and violence ended the dream of a 16-year-old girl in Cabatuan, Iloilo. "Glenda" talks about the early morning of February 14, 2019 when she saw the body of her daughter, "Ariza," lying in a pool of blood inside her room. Cabatuan, Iloilo police chief PCpt. Sullen Domingo gives information about the crime scene, and shares why they believe that the victim knew the person who killed her. “Glenda’s” neighbor “Mario” says he saw a half-naked man, later identified as 25-year-old Gringo Morales, fleeing from where the screams might have come on the night the victim died. Later, PCpt. Domingo details how Morales brutally killed “Ariza” after attempting to rape her.

xySB95Ky9T0.title: Rehabilitasyon o reklamasyon? Ika-2 yugto | Failon Ngayon
xySB95Ky9T0.description:
Taong 2006 idineklara na ng DENR bilang isa sa key biodiversity areas ng bansa ang karagatan ng Manila Bay. Dalawang taon ang nakalipas, naglabas naman ng desisyon ang Korte Suprema na linisin ang Manila Bay dahil sa kapabayaan ng iba’t ibang sektor na pangalagaan ito.

Pero hindi pa naman huli ang lahat kahit dalawang dekada na ang lumipas. Unti-unti, sa mga ginagawang pagpapasara ng mga establisyimento na lumalabag sa batas at sunod-sunod na clean-up may nakikita namang pagbabago sa kalidad ng tubig nito. 

May kanya-kanyang toka ang bawat isa gaya ng sa mga lokal na pamahalaan. Pero ang toka ng mga water concessionaires na sewerage treatment plant (o STP) para saluhin ang mga maruming tubig, hindi pa nila kumpletong nagagawa. 

Paano rin mangyayari ang lahat ng magandang adhikain kung balak namang magtayo ng halos 9,000 ektaryang reclamation projects sa mga baybayin ng Manila Bay? Isa na nga rito ang tuloy na tuloy na ang pagtatayo at 5 ang may environmental compliance certificates na. Pero ang mga Pilipinong siyentipiko ay may mga babala sa maaaring mangyaring mga sakuna sakaling magtambak ng lupa sa Manila Bay at patayuan ng nagtataasang gusali. Tulad ng land subsidence o pagbaba ng lupa, storm surge at mga pagbaha. 

Sa kalagayan ng Manila Bay ngayon, kung ikaw ang tatanungin, saan ka papabor? Sa rehabilitasyon o reklamasyon ng Manila Bay?


___


FAILON NGAYON, Sabado alas-11 ng gabi pagkatapos ng Pinoy Brother Otso sa ABS-CBN! 

Mapapanood ang replay ng FAILON NGAYON sa ANC tuwing Linggo, alas-2 ng hapon. 

Mag-kumento at ipahayag ang inyong saloobin sa aming official Facebook pages, http://www.facebook.com/failon.ngayon.fanpage.
 
I-follow din ang Failon Ngayon sa aming official Twitter account sa http://www.twitter.com/Failon_Ngayon o @Failon_Ngayon at gamitin ang hashtag na #FailonNgayon.

Maaari ding mapanood ang ibang segments at episodes ng Failon Ngayon sa Youtube at iwant! Bisitahin lamang ang www.youtube.com/abscbnnews at ang www.iwant.ph
